INSERT INTO `rcptable` VALUES ('rcp-003','acc-001','Bistek','beef,soysauce,lemon,garlic,onion,olive oil,water,salt','Marinate beef in soy sauce, lemon (or calamansi), and ground black pepper for at least 1 hour||Heat the cooking oil in a pan then pan-fry half of the onions until the texture becomes soft||Pan-fry the beef on the same pan where the onions were fried for 1 minute per side||Saute garlic and remaining raw onions until onion softens||Pour the remaining marinade and water. Bring to a boil||Add beef. Cover the pan and simmer until the meat is tender||Season with ground black pepper and salt as needed. Top with pan-fried onions','img-010','Meal','A simple yet delicious Filipino dish.','1 kg,5 tbsp,1 lemon,3 cloves,3 parts,4 tbsp,1 cup,1 pinch'),('rcp-004','acc-002','Tuna Nicoise','potatoes,olive oil,eggs,red wine vinegar,capers,sunflower oil,red onions,spinach,tuna','Heat oven to 200C/fan 180C/gas. Toss the potatoes with 2 tsp oil and some seasoning||Tip onto a large baking tray, then roast for 20 mins, stirring halfway, until crisp, golden and cooked through||Meanwhile, put eggs in a small pan of water, bring to the boil, then simmer for 8-10 mins, depending on how you like them cooked||Plunge into a bowl of cold water to cool for a few mins. Peel away the shells, then cut into halves||In a large salad bowl, whisk together the remaining oil, red wine vinegar, capers and chopped tomatoes||Season, tip in the onion, spinach, tuna and potatoes, then gently toss together||Top with the eggs, then serve straight away','img-011','Meal','A light and simple meal that is perfect for a quick lunch or dinner. It is a great way to use up leftover potatoes and tuna.','450 g,2 tbsp,4,2 tbsp,2 tbsp,50 g,1/2,100 g,400 g'),('rcp-005','acc-003','Pancakes','flour,eggs,milk,sunflower oil,sugar,raspberries,blueberries','Put the flour, eggs, milk, 1 tbsp oil and a pinch of salt into a bowl or large jug, then whisk to a smooth batter||Set aside for 30 mins to rest if you have time, or start cooking straight away||Set a medium frying pan or crêpe pan over a medium heat and carefully wipe it with some oiled kitchen paper||When hot, cook your pancakes for 1 min on each side until golden, keeping them warm in a low oven as you go||Serve with lemon wedges and sugar, or your favourite filling||Once cold, you can layer the pancakes between baking parchment, then wrap in cling film and freeze for up to 2 months','img-012','Dessert','A delicious dessert made with flour, eggs, milk, sunflower oil, sugar, raspberries, and blueberries. Perfect for a sweet treat or a breakfast option.','100 g,2,300 ml,1 tbsp,50 g,50 g,50 g'),('rcp-006','acc-004','Chocolate Raspberry Brownies','chocolate,milk chocolate,salted butter,light brown sugar,eggs,plain flour,cocoa,raspberries','Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas. Line a 20 x 30cm baking tray tin with baking parchment||Put the chocolate, butter and sugar in a pan and gently melt, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon. Remove from the heat||Stir the eggs, one by one, into the melted chocolate mixture. Sieve over the flour and cocoa, and stir in||Stir in half the raspberries, scrape into the tray, then scatter over the remaining raspberries||Bake on the middle shelf for 30 mins or, if you prefer a firmer texture, for 5 mins more||Cool before slicing into squares. Store in an airtight container for up to 3 days','img-013','Dessert','A classic dessert that combines the rich flavors of chocolate and raspberries. Perfect for a sweet treat after a meal or as a snack.','200 g,100 g,250 g,400 g,4,140 g,50 g,200 g'),('rcp-007','acc-005','Vegan Casserole','rapeseed oil,onion,garlic,paprika,cumin,medium carrots,small stalks celery,red pepper,yellow pepper,tomato,vegetable stock cube,courgettes,lentils','Heat the oil in a large, heavy-based pan. Add the onions and cook gently for 5 – 10 mins until softened||Add the garlic, spices, dried thyme, carrots, celery and peppers and cook for 5 minutes||Add the tomatoes, stock, courgettes and fresh thyme and cook for 20 - 25 minutes||Take out the thyme sprigs. Stir in the lentils and bring back to a simmer||Serve with wild and white basmati rice, mash or quinoa','img-014','Vegan','A hearty and comforting vegan casserole, perfect for a cold day.','1,1,3 cloves,1 tsp,1/2 tsp,1 tbsp,3,2,1,1,800 g,250 ml,2 sliced,250 g'),('rcp-008','acc-006','Mushroom & Chestnut Rotolo','mushrooms,chestnut,challot,garlic,rosemary,wild mushroom,soysauce,white wine,lasagne sheet,breadcrumbs,handful sage,truffle oil','Soak the dried mushrooms in 350ml boiling water and set aside until needed. Blitz ¾ of the chestnuts with 150ml water until creamy||Roughly chop the remaining chestnuts. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large non-stick frying pan||Fry the shallots with a pinch of salt until softened, then add the garlic, chopped chestnuts and rosemary, and fry for 2 mins more||Add the wild mushrooms, 2 tbsp oil and some seasoning. Cook for 3 mins until they begin to soften||Bring a large pan of salted water to the boil and get a large bowl of ice water ready||Spread a good spoonful of the sauce on the bottom two thirds of each sheet, then, rolling away from yourself, roll up the shorter ends','img-015','Vegan','A hearty, comforting Italian dish made with mushrooms, chestnuts, and wild mushrooms. Perfect for a cold day.','30 g,240 g,3,1 cloves,3 springs,500 g,2 tbsp,125 ml,350 g,4 tbsp,1/2,10 g'),('rcp-009','acc-007','Matar Paneer','sunflower oil,paneer,cumin,turmeric,coriander,green chili,large tomato,peas,garam masala,small bunch coriander,naan bread','Heat the oil in a frying pan over high heat until it’s shimmering hot. Add the paneer, then turn the heat down a little||Fry until it starts to brown at the edges, then turn it over and brown on each side – the paneer will brown faster than you think, so don’t walk away||Remove the paneer from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. Put the ginger, cumin, turmeric, ground coriander and chilli in the pan, and fry everything for 1 min||Add the tomatoes, mashing them with the back of a spoon and simmer everything for 5 mins until the sauce smells fragrant||Add a splash of water if it’s too thick. Season well. Add the peas and simmer for a further 2 mins, then stir in the paneer and sprinkle over the garam masala||Divide between two bowls, top with coriander leaves and serve with naan bread, roti or rice','img-016','Meal','Matar Paneer is a popular Indian dish made with paneer, a type of cheese, and a variety of spices. It is a great source of protein and is easy to make.','1 tbsp,225 g,2,1 tsp,1 tsp,1 tsp,1,4,150 g,1 tsp,1,3'),('rcp-010','acc-001','Squash Linguine','butternut squash,garlic,olive oil,linguine pasta,small bunch sage','Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas. Put the squash and garlic on a baking tray and drizzle with the olive oil||Roast for 35-40 mins until soft. Season. Cook the pasta according to pack instructions. Drain, reserving the water||Use a stick blender to whizz the squash with 400ml cooking water||Heat some oil in a frying pan, fry the sage until crisp, then drain on kitchen paper||Tip the pasta and sauce into the pan and warm through. Scatter with sage','img-017','Meal','A delicious squash linguine with a creamy squash sauce and crispy sage.','350 g,3,3 tbsp,350 g,1'),('rcp-011','acc-002','Vegetarian Chilli','roasted vegetable,kidney beans,chopped tomatoes,mixed grain','Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/ gas . Cook the vegetables in a casserole dish for 15 mins||Tip in the beans and tomatoes, season, and cook for another 10-15 mins until piping hot||Heat the pouch in the microwave on High for 1 min and serve with the chilli','img-018','Vegan','A delicious squash linguine with a creamy squash sauce and crispy sage.','400 g,1 can,1 can,1 packet'),('rcp-012','acc-003','Carrot Cake','rvegetable oil,plain flour,bicarbonate of soda,sugar,eggs,salt,cinnamon,grated carrots,walnuts,cream cheese,caster sugar,butter','For the carrot cake, preheat the oven to 160C/325F/Gas. Grease and line a 26cm/10in springform cake tin||Mix all of the ingredients for the carrot cake, except the carrots and walnuts, together in a bowl until well combined. Stir in the carrots and walnuts||Spoon the mixture into the cake tin and bake for 1 hour 15 minutes, or until a skewer inserted into the middle comes out clean||Remove the cake from the oven and set aside to cool for 10 minutes, then carefully remove the cake from the tin and set aside to cool completely on a cooling rack||Meanwhile, for the icing, beat the cream cheese, caster sugar and butter together in a bowl until fluffy. Spread the icing over the top of the cake with a palette knife','img-019','Dessert','A delicious squash linguine with a creamy squash sauce and crispy sage.','450 ml,400 g,2 tsp,550 ml,5 eggs,1/2 tsp,2 tsp,500 g,150 g,200 g,150 g,100 g'),('rcp-013','acc-004','Madeira Cake','butter,caster sugar,eggs,self-raising flour,milk,lemon,to glazed mixed peel','Pre-heat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4. Grease an 18cm/7in round cake tin, line the base with greaseproof paper and grease the paper||Cream the butter and sugar together in a bowl until pale and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating the mixture well between each one and adding a tablespoon of the flour with the last egg to prevent the mixture curdling||Sift the flour and gently fold in, with enough milk to give a mixture that falls slowly from the spoon. Fold in the lemon zest||Spoon the mixture into the prepared tin and lightly level the top. Bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 30-40 minutes, or until golden-brown on top and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean||Remove from the oven and set aside to cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn it out on to a wire rack and leave to cool completely. To serve, decorate the cake with the candied peel','img-020','Dessert','A moist and rich Madeira Cake, perfect for dessert. Made with butter, caster sugar, eggs, self-raising flour, milk, lemon, and candied peel.','175 g,175 g,3,250 g,3 tbsp,1,1'),('rcp-014','acc-005','Rock Cake','self-raising flour,caster sugar,baking powder,butter,dried fruit,eggs,milk,vanilla extract','Preheat oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4 and line a baking tray with baking parchment||Mix the flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl and rub in the cubed butter until the mixture looks like breadcrumbs, then mix in the dried fruit||In a clean bowl, beat the egg and milk together with the vanilla extract. Add the egg mixture to the dry ingredients and stir with a spoon until the mixture just comes together as a thick, lumpy dough||Add a teaspoon more milk if you really need it to make the mixture stick together. Place golfball-sized spoons of the mixture onto the prepared baking tray||Leave space between them as they will flatten and spread out to double their size during baking. Bake for 15-20 minutes, until golden-brown||Remove from the oven, allow to cool for a couple of minutes then turn them out onto a wire rack to cool','img-021','Dessert','Rock cake is a traditional British dessert made with self-raising flour, caster sugar, baking powder, butter, dried fruit, eggs, milk, and vanilla extract. It is a simple and delicious recipe.','225 g,75 g,1 tsp,125 g,150 g,1,1 tbsp,2 tsp'),('rcp-015','acc-006','Brie wrapped in Prosciutto & Brioche','plain flour,caster sugar,yeast,milk,large eggs,glaze eggs,butter,brie,prosciutto','Mix the flour, 1 tsp salt, caster sugar, yeast, milk and eggs together in a mixer using the dough attachment for 5 mins until the dough is smooth||Add the butter and mix for a further 4 mins on medium speed. Scrape the dough bowl and mix again for 1 min||Place the dough in a container, cover with cling film and leave in the fridge for at least 6 hrs before using||Wrap the Brie in the prosciutto and set aside. Turn out the dough onto a lightly floured surface. Roll into a 25cm circle||Place the wrapped Brie in the middle of the circle and fold the edges in neatly||Put the parcel onto a baking tray lined with baking parchment and brush with beaten egg||Chill in the fridge for 30 mins, then brush again with beaten egg and chill for a further 30 mins. Leave to rise for 1 hr at room temperature||Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6, then bake for 22 mins. Serve warm','img-022','Snacks','A delicious recipe for Brie wrapped in Prosciutto & Brioche. Perfect for a snack or a light lunch.','375 g,50 g,7 g,75 g,3,1,180 g,250 g,8 slices'),('rcp-016','acc-007','Boulangère Potatoes','onion,thyme,olive oil,potatoes,vegetable stock','Heat oven to 200C/fan 180C/gas. Fry the onions and thyme sprigs in the oil until softened and lightly coloured (about 5 mins)||Spread a layer of potatoes over the base of a 1.5-litre oiled gratin dish||Sprinkle over a few onions (see picture, above) and continue layering, finishing with a layer of potatoes||Pour over the stock and bake for 50-60 mins until the potatoes are cooked and the top is golden and crisp','img-023','Snacks','A delicious French dish of baked potatoes with onions and thyme. Serve as a snack or light meal.','2,springs,2 tbsp,1.5 kg,425 g'),('rcp-017','acc-001','Chivito Uruguayo','beef brisket,bread,lettuce,tomato,ham,mozzarella,bacon,egg,onion,pepper','Crush the meat so that it is finite and we put it on a griddle to brown it||Put the eggs, bacon and ham to fry||Cut the bread in half, put the beef brisket, the fried eggs, the bacon, the ham, the mozzarella, the tomato and the lettuce||Cover with the other half of the bread and serve','img-024','Snacks','A traditional Uruguayan dish made with beef brisket, bread, lettuce, tomato, ham, mozzarella, bacon, egg, onion, and pepper. It is a popular snack in Uruguay andis often served with a side of hot sauce.','2,2,1,1,100 g,100 g,100 g,1,1,0.5 g'),('rcp-018','acc-002','Fettuccine Alfredo','fettuccine,heavy cream,butter,parmesan,parsley,black pepper','Cook pasta according to package instructions in a large pot of boiling water and salt||Add heavy cream and butter to a large skillet over medium heat until the cream bubbles and the butter melts||Whisk in parmesan and add seasoning (salt and black pepper)||Let the sauce thicken slightly and then add the pasta and toss until coated in sauce. Garnish with parsley, and it\'s ready','img-025','Meal','A creamy and delicious Italian dish made with fettuccine pasta, heavy cream, and parmesan cheese. Perfect for a cozy dinner night.','1 lb,1/2 cup,1/2 cup,1/2 cup,2 tbsp,0.25 g'),('rcp-019','acc-003','Crispy Eggplant','large eggplant,breadcrumbs,sesame seed,eggs,salt,pepper,vegetable oil','Slice eggplant into 1 cm (0.4-inch) slices. Place them in a bowl and sprinkle them with salt. Allow them to sit for 30 minutes to render some of their liquid and bitterness||After 30 minutes wash eggplant slices from salt and pat dry with a kitchen towel.||In a large bowl/plate place breadcrumbs and sesame seeds. In another bowl beat 2 eggs with pinch salt and pepper.||Heat oil in a large skillet over high heat. Dip eggplant slices in egg, then in crumbs, and place in hot oil||Fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown. Drain on a paper towel','img-026','Snacks','Crispy eggplant is a popular snack in many parts of the world. It is a great way to enjoy a crunchy and savory treat. This recipe is easy to make and can be enjoyed as a snack or as a side dish with other meals.','1,1 cup,50 g,2,0.25 g,0.25 g,200 g'),('rcp-020','acc-004','Bread Omelette','bread,eggs,salt','Beat the eggs in a bowl and add salt to taste||Toast the bread to your desired level of crispiness||Place the beaten eggs on top of the toasted bread||Cover the pan and let the eggs cook for 2 to 3 minutes||Serve hot and enjoy!','img-027','Snacks','Simple and delicious bread omelette that can be enjoyed as a snack or breakfast','1 loaf,3 eggs,50 g,0.5 g'),('rcp-021','acc-005','Fasoliyyeh Bi Z-Zayt','green beans,olive oil,salt,garlic,cilantro','Place the green beans into a large pot, and drizzle with olive oil. Season with salt to taste, and put the lid on the pot||Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until beans are cooked to your desired doneness||The idea is not to saute them, but to let them steam in the moisture released by the ice crystals||Add cilantro and garlic to the beans, and continue to cook just until the cilantro has started to wilt||Eat as a main course by scooping up with warm pita bread or serve as a side dish','img-028','Vegan','A delicious and healthy recipe for fasoliyyeh bi z-zayt, a traditional Iranian dish made with green beans, olive oil, salt, garlic, and cilantro. This recipe is perfect for anyone who loves a hearty and flavorful side dish or main course. With its simple ingredients and easy-to-follow steps, this recipe is sure to become a favorite in your kitchen.','16 ounces,1/4 cup,0.5 g,1 clove,1/4 cup'),('rcp-022','acc-007','Warm Roast Asparagus Salad','asparagus,red wine vinegar,tomato,virgin olive oil,clear honey,potatoes,dijon mustard,basil','Preheat the oven to 200C/Gas 6/fan 180C. Snap off the woody ends of the asparagus and discard. Arrange the asparagus in a single layer in a baking tray with sides||Cut the tomatoes in half widthways, nestle them in with the asparagus, season with sea salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil||Roll each bacon rasher into a tight roll (if large, first cut in half crosswise), and arrange in the tray||Drizzle the bacon rolls with the honey and bake for 20 minutes until the tomatoes are soft and the bacon is crisp. In the meantime, boil the potatoes until tender||Whisk the vinegar, olive oil, mustard, some sea salt and pepper in a large bowl until blended. Toss the rocket or spinach leaves in half of the dressing, and arrange on a large serving platter||Drain the potatoes and cut in half. Gently toss them in the rest of the dressing, and arrange on the platter with the asparagus. Tuck in the tomatoes and bacon','img-029','Vegan','A delicious and healthy salad that is perfect for a light lunch or dinner. The combination of asparagus, tomatoes, and bacon makes for a savory and satisfying meal.','500 g,2 tbsp,4,1 tbsp,1 tsp,1 pack,1 tsp,100 g'),('rcp-023','acc-001','Iced Pumpkin Spice Latte','brewed espresso,whole milk,maple syrup,pumpkin puree,vanilla extract,pumpkin pie spice,salt,ice,whipped cream','Place espresso, milk, maple syrup, pumpkin, vanilla, pumpkin pie spice, and salt into the cup of a high-speed blender||Blend on High speed until fully smooth and combined, about 30 seconds||Fill a glass with ice. Pour pumpkin mixture over ice and serve cold. ||If desired, serve topped with whipped cream and an extra sprinkle of pumpkin pie spice','img-030','Drinks','A delicious and comforting fall drink that combines the flavors of pumpkin spice and latte. This recipe is perfect for a cozy evening by the fireplace or a quick breakfast on the go.','1 shot,1 cup,2 tbsp,2 tbsp,1/2 tsp,1/4 tsp,1 tsp,1 pinch,1 scoop,50 g'),('rcp-024','acc-002','Pomegranate Fizz','fresh basil,honey,fresh lime juice,pomegranate juice,club soda,ice cubes,lime wedge','In a shaker, add basil leaves with lime juice and agave syrup and mash with a cocktail muddler||Add pomegranate juice to the shaker and shake well||Fill a glass with ice cubes and strain shaker contents into the glass||Top with club soda and garnish with lime wedge','img-031','Drinks','A refreshing and sweet drink made with pomegranate juice, lime juice, and agave syrup. Perfect for a hot day or as a refreshing drink on a hot day.','5,1 tbsp,1 ounce,3 ounces,4 ounces,1 scoop,1'),('rcp-025','acc-003','Virgin Strawberry Daiquiri','chilled lemon-lime soda,white sugar,large strawberries,lemon juice,ice cubes','Gather the ingredients||Combine lemon-lime soda, sugar, strawberries, and lemon juice in a blender; add ice and blend until smooth||Pour into a fancy glass to serve','img-032','Drinks','A refreshing and sweet drink made with chilled lemon-lime soda, white sugar, large strawberries, lemon juice, and ice cubes. Perfect for a hot day or as a refreshing drink after a meal.','3/4 cup,1/4 cup,2,1 tbsp,4'),('rcp-026','acc-004','Watermelon and Strawberry Lemonade','watermelon,water,fresh strawberries,white sugar,fresh lemon juice','Combine watermelon, water, strawberries, sugar, and lemon juice in a blender; blend until smooth','img-033','Drinks','A refreshing drink made with watermelon, strawberries, sugar, and lemon juice. Perfect for a hot day or as a refreshing drink on a cold day.','8 cups,2 cups,1 cup,1/2 cup'),('rcp-027','acc-006','Gordon\'s Berry Breakfast Drink','chilled orange juice,chilled pineapple juice,vanilla yogurt,frozen blueberries,frozen sliced strawberries,sliced banana','Place the orange juice, pineapple juice, yogurt, blueberries, strawberries, and bananas into a blender. Cover and blend until smooth.||The berry drink will be very thick. Serve immediately','img-034','Drinks','A refreshing berry drink that is perfect for breakfast. This drink is packed with vitamins and antioxidants. It is also a great way to start your day with a healthy boost of energy.','3/4 cups,1/3 cup,2 cups,1 cup,1/2 cup,1/2');
